data.name: BtnSigFigs.ToolTip
data.value:
Toggle sig fig mode (Ctrl+Alt+F)
On (orange): Automatically detects and rounds numbers to sig figs when applicable Off (gray): Uses full precision during calculations
Tips: -Use sf(number,figures) to set the number of sig figs of a number manually -Use nosf(number) to make a number infinitely precise -Use getsf(number) to see the number of sif figs assigned to the number -This uses even/odd rounding (when last digit is 5, rounds up if odd, down if even)

data.name: BtnExplicit.ToolTip
data.value: Toggle explicit mode (Ctrl+Alt+T) On (orange): Variables must be declared with let/global/private/public before being used Off (gray): Variables can be used without being declared
